claim.claim-text:
2. A hybrid inflator for an inflating-type safety system of a vehicle provided with an air bag, which comprises an inflator housing, a gas generator provided in said inflator housing, and an ignition means chamber having an ignition means connected to said gas generator, wherein 
the interior of said inflator housing is filled with a pressurized medium containing an inert gas; 
said gas generator has an outer shell formed by a gas generator housing having a plurality of the first and second communication holes; 
said gas generator housing includes, therein, first and second gas generating chambers each having a gas generating agent; 
said first gas generating chamber and said inflator housing are in communication with each other through said first communication holes; said second gas generating chamber and said inflator housing are in communication with each other through said second communication holes; and 
each of said first and/or second communication holes has such a size that combustion gas generated in said first and/or second gas generating chamber can flow out therethrough but the gas generating agent can be prevented from leaking outwards.

3. A hybrid inflator for an inflating-type safety system of a vehicle provided with an air bag, which comprises an inflator housing, a gas generator provided in said inflator housing, and an ignition means chamber having an ignition means connected to said gas generator, wherein 
the interior of said inflator housing is filled with a pressurized medium containing an inert gas; 
said gas generator has an outer shell formed by a gas generator housing having a plurality of the first and second communication holes; 
said gas generator housing includes, therein, first and second gas generating chambers each having a gas generating agent; a first ignition means chamber having a first ignition means is connected to a first gas generating chamber; a second ignition means chamber having a second ignition means is connected to a second gas generating chamber; said first gas generating chamber and said inflator housing are in communication with each other through said first communication holes; said second gas generating chamber and said inflator housing are in communication with each other through said second communication holes; and 
each of said first and/or second communication holes has such a size that combustion gas generated in said first and/or second gas generating chamber can flow out therethrough but the gas generating agent can be prevented from leaking outwards, said second communication holes are disposed at a distance from said second ignition means in the widthwise direction and/or the longitudinal direction of said inflator housing.
